social_posts.post_text: I randomly booked two tickets to Vegas while at work a few weeks ago. Spent a few days in sin city with my Auntie. No filters, no camera, no itinerary, no desire film everything, just a fun, relaxing vacation with my aunt. I’ve made every vacation in the past 5 years about showing it off to the world. Not doing that was a good change of pace. Be present and mindful. Put the camera and phone down.
Merry Christmas from the whole fam damily.
First Arnold Classic Weekend was a success. I’m just happy to be here. WSM next with the sbd fam.

WSM finals day 1, greatest team on earth.

2024 accountability post:

Currently weighing 261lbs at roughly 5’11 and 29 years old. I’ve hated the skin I’m in for as long as I can remember. I’m super detrained and intentionally put on a ton of weight chasing huge gym lifts in the past, and have yet to really put in the work to shed the fat since then. I’m posting this because I don’t care what anyone thinks of my body or appearance, but I’m trying to improve. I’ve made posts like this in years past but quickly hid them after someone in an online argument has defaulted to calling me fat, or so a perspective dating candidate wouldn’t see what I look like without a shirt or while I’m not holding some heavy weight on a barbell. I will be leaving this one up. Goal weight is 210lbs. I don’t have a time frame I’d like to achieve that in, but I do need to be under 230 for South Carolina’s Strongest Man in April.

I can’t continue to hate myself and make no changes, so here’s to major change in 2024.

I wish you all the best in your endeavors this year. The hardest part is starting, so let this post serve as a reminder to get started on your own goals.

Much love
